<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Enorr da Mage on 08-18-2001 05:36 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">IDEAS for money:

As a web developer / eq fanatic / programmer / entrepreneur / and eqatlas lover!

- I have a few ideas for some moola for atlas man / who has saved my bacon hundreds of times! - thanks to the coordinate system printed on the eqatlas maps!


First, 
 ... the CD idea is good but also consider a 'complete atlas download' (possibly a PDF doc or set of map image files) that contain the entire archive of current Atlas maps... (high speed connect players would jump at this one too!) --
charge a credit card to download the file.  Maybe even throw in some divider sections with 'zone connect maps' in the download for those that want to print the entire sucka out to a binder (me!)&gt;

-- dynamically create the "download file" with the latest updated maps using a cron job to pull all the maps and assemble the file every day -- (so you don't have to mess with it as much) -- this way the document is always current with the latest maps!

An alternative payment option here is to allow those that pay a yearly 'registration' fee to have access to this 'download file' with the entire atlas as well as (possibly) the option for the atlas to be mailed to them on CD.

Second,
 ... convince Verant to offer a 'survey' (one of those 'after patch' survey things that we see occasionally) and have them ask players if they have ever used eqatlas?  Let them be their own judge as to how important this site is to THEIR business - after they get thousands of 'yes' replies.  Ask for some financial help from them since you are supporting their business in a BIG way!

Just a couple if ideas that have worked for friends of mine and myself. 

Good luck and thanks for all you do!

WebManTimbo@hotmail.com
</TEXTAREA>
